Pompeianus, the virtuous husband of Lucilla, was the only senator

who asserted the honour of his rank. As a father, he permitted his sons to consult their safety by attending the amphitheatre. As a Roman, he declared, that his own life was in the emperor’s hands, but that he would never behold the son of Marcus prostituting his person and dignity. Notwithstanding his manly resolution, Pom- peianus escaped the resentment of the tyrant, and, with his honour, had the good fortune to preserve his life ⁴².
